    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>A natural earth brown pigment ranging in color from a dark yellow to a deep reddish brown, containing silica, clay, and a mixture of iron oxides along with small amounts of manganese dioxide. It may be called "umber" or "sienna," depending on its color.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
